Recently I've found myself in the care of a Singer “Zig-zag” Sewing Machine
Model 247 from the mid-70s built into a table. I'm not a fan of the aesthetics
of the enclosure as it has all the appearances of a cabinet without the drawers
part. If I was designing this I'd rather just not have an ornate handle on the
front at all (because it's not a drawer) but I'm not one to turn down a free
sewing machine. The copyright date on the manual is 1975.

