My machine is controlled by a foot-pedal allowing me to drive the belt with
variable speed. I made sure that the fabric stayed taut by holding onto both
ends as I worked my way down each side, pivoting the workpiece around the bottom
corner, then up the other side, all the while keeping an eye out for any puckers
or pleats in the fabric caused by irregularities in its weave or uneven
stretching.

Once both legs are hemmed cut away any excess thread and press the hems with an
iron to strengthen the stitch.

